I think the ending -coe indicates that the word is a shape (similar to greek: τρί-γωνο, τετρά-γωνο etc). 
I would say that the zeti-, wopi-, gafi-, buvi-, are "alien" numbers indicating the number of angles of each shape.
I made notes on a paper.
I had a problem figuring out whether i should pick buviicoh and/or buvicoe.
